      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "Concept ACK\r\n\r\nInteresting find. I was very confused at first why there wouldn't be further writes on this passed hashing object within `secp256k1_ellswift_elligatorswift_var`, but it's just copied over to a new instance for each `secp256k1_ellswift_prng` call (which makse sense for reusing the state with different counters):\r\nhttps://github.com/bitcoin-core/secp256k1/blob/13db747f2b558659b26f8ca3f5ea6e6d34e2054c/src/modules/ellswift/main_impl.h#L310-L311\r\n\r\nFwiw Bitcoin Core's BIP324 implementation is not affected by this, as we [pass in the randomness](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/1aafd49077041e874d6b5f114927bc37e5b85d71/src/key.cpp#L320) (`auxrnd32` parameter), which IIUC overwrites the secret key in the `_sha256` object buffer.",
